INLINE CSS - styles 
   DO NOT do inline CSS if youre doing the whole page.
   list of styles
      - background-color = explains itself
      - border-style = border around tag
      - border-color = color of border
      - border-radius = gives border curve; must say px
      - text-shadow = gives text shadow 
      - font-size = changes font size

   <body style="background-color: blue">
         </body>
   OR
   <body style="background-color: #256AD0">
         </body>
   OR
   <body style="background-color: rgb(38,113,235)">
         </body>
   - put the style= WITHIN the first tag 

INTERNAL CSS
   gives place to put all CSS style changes in the head so its not tedius
   <style>
      body{
         whatever green part is; the style
      }
      .shadow-text {
         this creates a CLASS so you can add it to the lines,
         like if there are multiple paragraphs. 
         refer inline by class="shadow-text"
      }
      #large-paragraph{
         id selector
      }
   </style>

EXTERNAL CSS
   best way to do it. have its own file
   then it can update teh styles on each page and reduce manually
   redoing anything and reduce time/tedious effort
   - add into heading:
         <link rel="stylesheet" href="Styles.css">

BASIC PROPERTIES
   color: gray;
   background-color: blue;
   border-style: dashed; (dotted, etc)
   border-width: 3px;
   border-color: red;
   border-radius: 4px;
   height: 200px;
   text-align: center; (justify, etc)

CSS FLOAT
   can float info left or right of content
   img{ (or whatever tag you choose)
      float: right;
   }

CSS PSUEDO CLASSES
   styled based on current state, like hovering mouse, or every third list item
      [CLASS]:hover{
         background-color: red; = when your mouse hovers over the class in website,
         it turns red 
      } 
   [CLASS]:nth-child(DISTINCTION) { like tr every even}


STYLING A TABLE 
      rgb(x,x,x) MUST not have any spaces or it wont work
      rgba(x,x,x,x) - last one is transperany/opacity


COMMAND LINE INTERFACE (CLI) 
      ls = shows current directory
      cd = change directory  
         cd .. = goes back one directory
         cd ../.. = goes back two directories
         cd /[NAME] = goes into folder in directory
      mkdir = creates new directory. Do mkdir [NAME] and itll create [NAME]
      cp = copy of a file or directory
         e.g. copy file test.txt, do cp test.text testcopy.txt 
      mv = moves file or directory to another location
      pwd = displays path of current directory
      touch = create new file

GITHUB
      git = versio ncontrol system that tracks changes and help collaborate
      github = web based platform; collaboration platform
      repository = repo; command line is stored

   git status = check status
   git add = add files/folders, use . to add all
   git commit -m "words" = add a comment 
   git push = publish it to github

   in computer folder, hit command+shift+. = 
      shows hidden folder

GRADIENT IN WORDS 
   background-image: linear-gradient(#ffffff, black);
         background-clip: text;
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;